-- Eaton to sell division to Safran for $270 mln
-- By Ryan Vlastelica
-- Mon Jan 20, 2014 10:34AM EST
-- None



NEW YORK, Jan 20 (Reuters) - Eaton Corp <ETN.N> on Monday said it would sell its aerospace power distribution unit to Safran SA <SAF.PA> for $270 million, in a deal that is expected to close in the first half of 2014.

The division makes switches and power distribution items for use in aerospace systems, including cockpits, Eaton said in a statement. The unit had sales of about $102 million in 2013.